name: methyl 3-[bis(methylsulfanyl)methyl]-4-cyano-2-hydroxy-2,5-diphenylcyclopent-3-ene-1-carboxylate
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-1667
Reason: 3-Nitrophenyl group introduces a significant dipole, increasing intermolecular forces and melting point by approximately +50°C. The methyl group reduces the melting point by approximately -10°C due to the reduced molecular weight and van der Waals interactions. The sulfur atom within the methylsulfanyl group introduces a rigid structure, which can participate in dipole interactions and raise the melting point by approximately +10°C. The cyano group introduces a significant dipole, increasing intermolecular forces and melting point by approximately +30°C. The phenyl group introduces additional rigidity and pi-pi interactions, raising the melting point by approximately +30°C. The carbonyl group introduces polar carbonyl interactions, raising the melting point by approximately +40°C. The hydroxyl group introduces additional rigidity and hydrogen bonding potential, raising the melting point by approximately +20°C. The diphenyl ether introduces additional rigidity and pi-pi interactions, raising the melting point by approximately +30°C. The methyl group reduces the melting point by approximately -10°C due to the reduced molecular weight and van der Waals interactions.
